article.description: — Tyrese Martin score 20 points and UConn defeated Butler 63-51 on Tuesday night.
article.headline: Martin scores 20 to lift UConn past Butler 63-51
article.linkText: Martin scores 20 to lift UConn past Butler 63-51
article.story: STORRS, Conn. -- — Tyrese Martin score 20 points and UConn defeated Butler 63-51 on Tuesday night. R.J. Cole scored 11 points for the Huskies (8-3, 5-3 Big East Conference) and Isaiah Whaley rejected seven shots on the defensive end. Bryce Golden scored 19 points for the Bulldogs (5-8, 4-6) and Bryce Nze snagged nine rebounds. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
